# <Project> — UI Style Guide: native desktop

**Per-kind дополнение к `ui-style-guide-base.md`.** Правила для desktop приложений на macOS / Windows / Linux. Native приложение должно ощущаться native на каждой OS — window chrome, menu bar, keyboard shortcuts, file dialogs.

Если есть backend — параллельно `ui-style-guide-backend.md`.

---

## 1. Platform conventions — primary source

- **macOS** — [Apple Human Interface Guidelines (macOS)](https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/designing-for-macos)
- **Windows** — [Windows 11 design guidelines](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/apps/design/) / Fluent Design
- **Linux** — GNOME HIG / KDE HIG (зависит от target DE; обычно следуем GNOME для GTK / KDE для Qt)

Cross-platform приложения **адаптируются** к conventions каждой OS, не делают one-size-fits-all. Меню бар вверху на macOS, в окне на Windows / Linux. Cmd vs Ctrl. Native file dialogs.

---

## 2. Window chrome + traffic lights

### 2.1. macOS

- **Traffic lights** (close / minimize / fullscreen) — top-left, **никогда** не кастомизируем расположение
- Title bar — толщина системная; custom titlebar возможен но осторожно (`NSWindow.titlebarAppearsTransparent`)
- **Vibrancy / blur** — для sidebar'ов (NSVisualEffectView), но sparingly
- **Toolbar** — system NSToolbar для primary actions

### 2.2. Windows

- **Caption buttons** (minimize / maximize / close) — top-right
- **Mica / Acrylic** material для модерн look (Windows 11 / WinUI 3)
- **Title bar** can be extended (custom content) но system controls должны remain
- **Command bar** для primary actions (Fluent)

### 2.3. Linux (GTK / KDE)

- **Client-side decorations** (GTK / GNOME) — header bar совмещает title + toolbar
- **Server-side decorations** (KDE) — традиционный title bar + toolbar separately
- Detect environment и адаптироваться (`XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP`)

### 2.4. Cross-platform consistency

Каждая OS — свои window conventions. Custom title bar — только если он добавляет value (например, integrated tab bar как в browser'ах). Не для эстетики.

---

## 3. Menu bar

### 3.1. macOS

- **Global menu bar** вверху экрана — обязателен для каждого app
- Стандартные menu items: App menu (About, Preferences, Quit), File, Edit, View, Window, Help — порядок и наличие согласно HIG
- **Cmd+Q** quit, **Cmd+W** close window, **Cmd+,** preferences — никогда не переопределяем

### 3.2. Windows / Linux

- **In-window menu bar** (или command bar / hamburger menu для современных Windows apps)
- **Alt key** активирует mnemonics — поддерживаем
- **Ctrl+Q** или **Alt+F4** для quit (платформа-specific)

### 3.3. Context menus

- macOS: secondary click / Control+click
- Windows: right click / Menu key
- Linux: right click

Контент context menu — relevant к target object, не общий app menu.

---

## 4. Keyboard shortcuts

### 4.1. Modifier keys

| Действие | macOS | Windows / Linux |
|---|---|---|
| Primary | Cmd | Ctrl |
| Alt | Option | Alt |
| Secondary | Control | (нет; не использовать) |

### 4.2. Стандартные shortcuts (никогда не переопределяем)

| Действие | Shortcut |
|---|---|
| Quit | Cmd+Q / Alt+F4 |
| Close window | Cmd+W / Ctrl+W |
| Save | Cmd+S / Ctrl+S |
| Open | Cmd+O / Ctrl+O |
| New | Cmd+N / Ctrl+N |
| Cut / Copy / Paste | Cmd+X/C/V / Ctrl+X/C/V |
| Undo / Redo | Cmd+Z / Cmd+Shift+Z / Ctrl+Z / Ctrl+Y |
| Find | Cmd+F / Ctrl+F |
| Preferences | Cmd+, (macOS only — в Windows нет конвенции) |

### 4.3. App-specific shortcuts

- Документируем в Help / Cheat Sheet
- Visible в menu items (`Cmd+S` после "Save" в меню)
- Discoverable — не hidden Easter eggs

### 4.4. Disclosure

`?` или `Cmd+/` показывает modal cheat sheet с shortcuts (опционально).

---

## 5. File dialogs + native pickers

- **Open / Save** — system file dialog (NSOpenPanel / Windows IFileDialog / GTK FileChooser). **Никогда** custom file browser inside app.
- **Recent files** — system mechanism (NSDocumentController на macOS, JumpList на Windows)
- **Drag and drop** files — поддерживаем через system DnD APIs
- **Paste image / file from clipboard** — стандартная operation

---

## 6. Multi-window

### 6.1. Когда multi-window:

- Document-based apps (TextEdit, Pages model)
- Side panels — отдельные окна как опция (Inspector window)
- Multi-window для multi-display setups

### 6.2. Когда single-window:

- Tool / utility apps
- Settings panels

### 6.3. Window restoration

- macOS: NSUserActivity / system state restoration
- Windows: JumpList + ApplicationView state
- Cross-platform: serialize window state (size, position, content) в user data dir, restore at launch

### 6.4. Multi-display

- Position windows на logical display, не screen pixel coords
- Respect display arrangement (primary, secondary)
- Adapt к display brightness / theme changes (system event listeners)

---

## 7. Theming — light / dark / system

### 7.1. Detection

- **macOS:** `NSAppearance` / SwiftUI `@Environment(\.colorScheme)` / Electron `nativeTheme.shouldUseDarkColors`
- **Windows:** `UISettings.GetColorValue` / WinUI Resource theme / `SystemParametersInfo`
- **Linux:** XDG settings (`org.freedesktop.appearance.color-scheme` через D-Bus в GNOME; KDE color scheme через `kdeglobals`)

### 7.2. User override

В Settings — 3 опции: Light / Dark / System (default).

### 7.3. Reactive theme switching

При system theme change — UI обновляется без restart (subscribe на system notifications).

---

## 8. Adaptivity — window resize, density, scaling

### 8.1. Window resize

- **Minimum window size** определена (например, 600×400)
- **Resizable** по default (если не fixed utility window)
- Content reflows: panels collapse, multi-column grid → single column при narrow

### 8.2. Display scaling

- **macOS:** Retina (2x) автоматически + Display Scaling user preference
- **Windows:** DPI awareness — обязательно `<dpiAware>True/PM</dpiAware>` в manifest (per-monitor DPI)
- **Linux:** `GDK_SCALE` / Qt scaling environment variables; respect system setting

### 8.3. Font scaling

- macOS: `NSFont.systemFont` adapts to user preferences
- Windows: respect `User text size` setting (Accessibility)
- Linux: respect `Xft.dpi` / GTK/Qt font scaling

### 8.4. Adaptive UI

| Window size | Адаптация |
|---|---|
| < 600px wide | Sidebar collapses → hamburger / overlay |
| Multi-column → single column |
| Toolbar items → overflow menu |
| Compact mode (some panes hidden) |

---

## 9. Color contrast + Accessibility

### 9.1. macOS

- **VoiceOver** — `accessibilityLabel`, `accessibilityHint`, `accessibilityRole`
- **Full Keyboard Access** — `Tab` навигация ко всем controls (не только text fields)
- **High Contrast** — `NSAccessibility.increaseContrast`
- **Reduce Motion** — `NSAccessibility.reduceMotion`

### 9.2. Windows

- **Narrator** — UIA (UI Automation) framework; AutomationProperties в WinUI/WPF
- **High Contrast mode** — особый theme; SystemParameters.HighContrast
- **Magnifier compatible** — focus indicators visible

### 9.3. Linux

- **Orca screen reader** — AT-SPI 2 (Assistive Technology Service Provider Interface)
- **GTK** / **Qt** имеют built-in accessibility — Accessible Name / Description

### 9.4. Keyboard navigation full

Каждый interactive control доступен через Tab. **Никогда** `tabindex` пропусков. Focus indicator всегда visible.

### 9.5. Color contrast

WCAG AA для обеих тем. Особое внимание на selection / hover / focus states.

---

## 10. System integration

### 10.1. Notifications

- **macOS:** UserNotifications framework / NSUserNotification (deprecated)
- **Windows:** Windows.UI.Notifications (Toast notifications)
- **Linux:** libnotify / D-Bus `org.freedesktop.Notifications`

Cross-platform libs: Electron `Notification`, Tauri `notification` plugin.

### 10.2. Dock / Taskbar

- **macOS:** Dock badges (`NSApp.dockTile.badgeLabel`), bouncing (sparingly), menu items in dock
- **Windows:** Taskbar progress, jump list, badges (Windows 11)
- **Linux:** Unity launcher API (legacy), `XEmbed`, free-desktop spec

### 10.3. System tray / menu bar extras

- **macOS:** `NSStatusItem` для menu bar
- **Windows:** System tray icon (System.Windows.Forms.NotifyIcon в WPF / WinUI 3 differs)
- **Linux:** `StatusNotifierItem` (D-Bus); legacy `Gtk.StatusIcon` for older DE

### 10.4. URL schemes / deep linking

- macOS: `Info.plist` `CFBundleURLTypes`
- Windows: protocol registration через app manifest
- Linux: `.desktop` file `MimeType=x-scheme-handler/<scheme>`

### 10.5. Auto-update

- **macOS:** Sparkle (open-source) / App Store auto-update
- **Windows:** WinSparkle / MSIX auto-update / Microsoft Store
- **Linux:** distribution package managers (apt / dnf / pacman) или AppImage / Flatpak / Snap updates

---

## 11. Loading и async (отзывчивость)

Принципы — `ui-style-guide-base.md` § 1 (принцип 2). Desktop-specific:

- **Indeterminate progress:** spinner (NSProgressIndicator / ProgressBar)
- **Determinate progress:** progress bar с % и ETA
- **Background tasks** — отображаются в системе (dock badge / taskbar progress)
- **Cancellation:** обязательно для long-running tasks
- **Toast / notification на завершение** background задачи (когда пользователь свернул)

---

## 12. Frameworks-first для desktop

### 12.1. Native

| Platform | Framework |
|---|---|
| macOS | SwiftUI (default modern) / AppKit (mature stacks) |
| Windows | WinUI 3 (modern) / WPF (mature) |
| Linux | GTK4 (GNOME) / Qt 6 (Qt apps / KDE) |

### 12.2. Cross-platform (с native feel)

| Framework | Trade-offs |
|---|---|
| **Tauri** (Rust + web frontend) | Small bundle, native webview, secure default. Recommended для new cross-platform. |
| **Electron** (Node + Chromium) | Large bundle, mature ecosystem, full Node. Used by VS Code, Discord, Slack. |
| **Flutter (Desktop)** | Custom rendering, one codebase, не native widgets но performant. |
| **Compose Multiplatform** | Kotlin, Compose-based, growing ecosystem. |
| **Qt** (C++/Python) | Native-looking, mature, license considerations (LGPL / commercial). |

### 12.3. Не пишем сами

| Категория | Готовое решение |
|---|---|
| Auto-update | Sparkle / WinSparkle / Tauri updater |
| Crash reporting | Sentry / Crashpad |
| Persistence | SQLite (через native bindings или driver) / Core Data (macOS) |
| Settings storage | NSUserDefaults / Registry / GSettings |
| Logging | OSLog / EventLog / journald |
| Networking | URLSession / WinHTTP / libcurl / framework-built-in |
| i18n | gettext / NSLocalizedString / Qt linguist |

---

## 13. Дистрибуция

- **macOS:** App Store + (опц.) outside-store with **notarization** обязательной (Gatekeeper). DMG / pkg installer.
- **Windows:** Microsoft Store + MSIX / MSI / EXE installer. Code signing обязательно (SmartScreen).
- **Linux:** Distribution packages (deb / rpm / Arch package), AppImage, Flatpak (Flathub), Snap.

Каждая платформа — свои store policies + signing requirements.

---

## 14. Desktop-specific checklist

В дополнение к `ui-style-guide-base.md` § 7:

- [ ] Platform conventions respected per OS (HIG / Fluent / GNOME-KDE HIG)
- [ ] Native window chrome (traffic lights / caption buttons / CSD / SSD)
- [ ] Native menu bar (global on macOS / in-window on Win/Linux)
- [ ] Standard keyboard shortcuts respected (Cmd+S / Ctrl+S, etc)
- [ ] App-specific shortcuts visible в menu items
- [ ] Native file dialogs (Open / Save / FileChooser)
- [ ] Light + Dark + System theme support с reactive switching
- [ ] DPI / scaling awareness (per-monitor DPI on Windows; Retina on macOS)
- [ ] Min window size + resize behavior + adaptive UI
- [ ] Multi-window / window restoration (если applicable)
- [ ] Accessibility — VoiceOver / Narrator / Orca labels
- [ ] Full keyboard navigation (Tab ко всем controls)
- [ ] High contrast / Reduced motion respected
- [ ] System integration — notifications / dock / tray / URL schemes
- [ ] Auto-update mechanism (если applicable)
- [ ] Code signing + notarization (где требуется)
